<p class="pull-left small mrgn-bttm-0"><strong>You may be looking for:</strong></p>
<ul class="pull-left mrgn-lft-md list-unstyled small">
  <li><a href="https://cra-design.github.io/gst-hst-business/exit-intent.html?uri=https://www.canada.ca/en/revenue-agency/services/e-services/digital-services-individuals/netfile-overview/eligibility.html">Netfile access code for personal income tax</a><br>
    <a href="https://cra-design.github.io/gst-hst-business/exit-intent.html?uri=https://apps.cra-arc.gc.ca/ebci/njwc/waconline/entry?request_locale=en">Web access code for filing information returns (for example T4, T4a, T5)</a></li>
</ul>
<div class="clearfix">&nbsp;</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-8">
    <p>The GST/HST access code is a four-digit access code is required for <strong>some</strong> GST/HST filing methods. It acts as a personal security key that authenticates you when you are not logged into a CRA account, and should not be shared with unauthorized individuals.</p>
  <!--  <p>
      <mark> Is the GST/HST access code a different code than the access code used for individual filing? If not, something should be explained about it here.</mark>
    </p>-->
    <p>Your GST/HST access code will remain the same for all filing periods unless you change it.</p>
    <h2 id="ccss_cd_rqrd">When you need an access code</h2>
   <!-- <p>CRA's sign-in services such as <a href="https://cra-design.github.io/gst-hst-business/exit-intent.html?uri=https://www.canada.ca/en/revenue-agency/services/e-services/digital-services-businesses/business-account.html">My Business Account</a> and Represent a client <strong>do not</strong> require the use of a GST/HST access code, they are more secure and provide additional services.</p>-->
<p>You do <strong>not</strong> always need an access code for filing electronically.</p>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <p>You do <strong>do not need an access code</strong> if you are filing:</p>
        <ul class="fa-ul">
          <li><span class="fas fa-times text-danger fa-li"></span>In your online CRA account (My Business Account or Represent a Client)</li>
          <li><span class="fas fa-times text-danger fa-li"></span>Through a participating Canadian financial institution</li>
          <li><span class="fas fa-times text-danger fa-li"></span>By mail</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <p>You <strong>do</strong> need an access code if you are filing:</p>
        <ul class="fa-ul">
          <li><span class="fas fa-check text-success fa-li"></span>Using the online NETFILE form (outside of a CRA account)</li>
            <li><span class="fas fa-check text-success fa-li"></span>Using third-party accounting software (GST/HST Internet File Transfer)</li>
          <li><span class="fas fa-check text-success fa-li"></span>Using GST/HST TELEFILE</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
          <p>A representative that is legally authorized to sign the paper copy of your GST/HST return may also use your access code to file on your behalf</a>.</p>

    <h2>How to get or change an access code</h2>
      <p>If you lose or forget your access code, or want to change your access code for other reasons, you can get a new code online.</p>
      <p>If you are a new GST/HST registrant and have never received an access code, phone us to get an access code. An existing access code can also be changed over the phone.</p>
    <h3>Online</h3>
      <p>You can set a new access code using <a href="https://cra-design.github.io/gst-hst-business/exit-intent.html?uri=https://www.canada.ca/en/revenue-agency/services/e-services/digital-services-businesses/gst-hst-internet-file-transfer/gst-hst-internet-file-transfer-need-access-code.html">GST/HST Access Code Online</a>.
        <p>Your new access code can be a number you choose, and you can use it to file all future GST/HST returns.</p>
    <p>To change your GST/HST access code, you will need to enter your business number and information from a previously filed return, either:
        <ul>
          <li>The reporting period and line 109 (net tax) where the amount on line 109 is not $0.00</li>
          <li>The reporting period and confirmation number from a return filed using GST/HST NETFILE, TELEFILE, or Internet File Transfer</li>
        </ul></p>

    <h3>By phone</h3>
    <p>
      <mark>Explain when an access code is created and/or sent to registrants initially</mark>
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>To get or change a GST/HST access code, call us at <span class="nowrap">1-800-959-5525.</span></li>
      <li>If calling from outside Canada and the United States, call collect at <span class="nowrap">613-940-8497.</span></li>
    </ul>

      
  </div>
</div>
